pokedex.name: bulbasaur
pokedex.flavor_text:
A strange seed was
planted on its
back at birth. The plant sprouts
and grows with
this POKÃ©MON.

pokedex.name: ivysaur
pokedex.flavor_text:
When the bulb on
its back grows
large, it appears to lose the
ability to stand
on its hind legs.

pokedex.name: venusaur
pokedex.flavor_text:
The plant blooms
when it is
absorbing solar energy. It stays
on the move to
seek sunlight.

pokedex.name: charmander
pokedex.flavor_text:
Obviously prefers
hot places. When
it rains, steam is said to spout
from the tip of
its tail.

pokedex.name: charmeleon
pokedex.flavor_text:
When it swings
its burning tail,
it elevates the temperature to
unbearably high
levels.

pokedex.name: charizard
pokedex.flavor_text:
Spits fire that
is hot enough to
melt boulders. Known to cause
forest fires
unintentionally.

pokedex.name: squirtle
pokedex.flavor_text:
After birth, its
back swells and
hardens into a shell. Powerfully
sprays foam from
its mouth.

pokedex.name: wartortle
pokedex.flavor_text:
Often hides in
water to stalk
unwary prey. For swimming fast, it
moves its ears to
maintain balance.

pokedex.name: blastoise
pokedex.flavor_text:
A brutal POKÃ©MON
with pressurized
water jets on its shell. They are
used for high
speed tackles.

pokedex.name: caterpie
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its short feet are tipped with suction
pads that enable it to tirelessly climb
slopes and walls.

pokedex.name: metapod
pokedex.flavor_text:
This POKÃ©MON is
vulnerable to
attack while its shell is soft,
exposing its weak
and tender body.

pokedex.name: butterfree
pokedex.flavor_text:
In battle, it
flaps its wings
at high speed to release highly
toxic dust into
the air.

pokedex.name: weedle
pokedex.flavor_text:
Often found in
forests, eating
leaves. It has a sharp
venomous stinger
on its head.

pokedex.name: kakuna
pokedex.flavor_text:
Almost incapable
of moving, this
POKÃ©MON can only harden its shell
to protect itself
from predators.

pokedex.name: beedrill
pokedex.flavor_text:
It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and
its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.

pokedex.name: pidgey
pokedex.flavor_text:
A common sight in
forests and woods.
It flaps its wings at ground
level to kick up
blinding sand.

pokedex.name: pidgeotto
pokedex.flavor_text:
Very protective
of its sprawling
territorial area, this POKÃ©MON will
fiercely peck at
any intruder.

pokedex.name: pidgeot
pokedex.flavor_text:
When hunting, it
skims the surface
of water at high speed to pick off
unwary prey such
as MAGIKARP.

pokedex.name: rattata
pokedex.flavor_text:
Bites anything
when it attacks.
Small and very quick, it is a
common sight in
many places.

pokedex.name: raticate
pokedex.flavor_text:
It uses its whisÂ­
kers to maintain
its balance. It apparently
slows down if
they are cut off.

pokedex.name: spearow
pokedex.flavor_text:
It flaps its small wings busily to
fly. Using its beak, it searches
in grass for prey.

pokedex.name: fearow
pokedex.flavor_text:
With its huge and
magnificent wings,
it can keep aloft without ever
having to land
for rest.

pokedex.name: ekans
pokedex.flavor_text:
Moves silently
and stealthily.
Eats the eggs of birds, such as
PIDGEY and
SPEAROW, whole.

pokedex.name: arbok
pokedex.flavor_text:
It is rumored that
the ferocious
warning markings on its belly
differ from area
to area.

pokedex.name: pikachu
pokedex.flavor_text:
When several of
these POKÃ©MON
gather, their electricity could
build and cause
lightning storms.

pokedex.name: raichu
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself
from its own high-voltage power.

pokedex.name: sandshrew
pokedex.flavor_text:
Burrows deep
underground in
arid locations far from water.
It only emerges
to hunt for food.

pokedex.name: sandslash
pokedex.flavor_text:
Curls up into a
spiny ball when
threatened. It can roll while
curled up to
attack or escape.

pokedex.name: nidoran-f
pokedex.flavor_text:
Although small,
its venomous
barbs render this POKÃ©MON dangerous.
The female has
smaller horns.

pokedex.name: nidorina
pokedex.flavor_text:
The female's horn
develops slowly.
Prefers physical attacks such as
clawing and
biting.

pokedex.name: nidoqueen
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its hard scales
provide strong
protection. It uses its hefty
bulk to execute
powerful moves.

pokedex.name: nidoran-m
pokedex.flavor_text:
Stiffens its ears
to sense danger.
The larger its horns, the more
powerful its
secreted venom.

pokedex.name: nidorino
pokedex.flavor_text:
An aggressive
POKÃ©MON that is
quick to attack. The horn on its
head secretes a
powerful venom.

pokedex.name: nidoking
pokedex.flavor_text:
It uses its
powerful tail in
battle to smash, constrict, then
break the prey's
bones.

pokedex.name: clefairy
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its magical and
cute appeal has
many admirers. It is rare and
found only in
certain areas.

pokedex.name: clefable
pokedex.flavor_text:
A timid fairy
POKÃ©MON that is
rarely seen. It will run and hide
the moment it
senses people.

pokedex.name: vulpix
pokedex.flavor_text:
At the time of
birth, it has
just one tail. The tail splits
from its tip as
it grows older.

pokedex.name: ninetales
pokedex.flavor_text:
Very smart and
very vengeful.
Grabbing one of its many tails
could result in a
1000-year curse.

pokedex.name: jigglypuff
pokedex.flavor_text:
When its huge eyes
light up, it sings
a mysteriously soothing melody
that lulls its
enemies to sleep.

pokedex.name: wigglytuff
pokedex.flavor_text:
The body is soft
and rubbery. When
angered, it will suck in air and
inflate itself to
an enormous size.

pokedex.name: zubat
pokedex.flavor_text:
Forms colonies in
perpetually dark
places. Uses ultrasonic waves
to identify and
approach targets.

pokedex.name: golbat
pokedex.flavor_text:
Once it strikes,
it will not stop
draining energy from the victim
even if it gets
too heavy to fly.

pokedex.name: oddish
pokedex.flavor_text:
During the day,
it keeps its face
buried in the ground. At night,
it wanders around
sowing its seeds.

pokedex.name: gloom
pokedex.flavor_text:
The fluid that
oozes from its
mouth isn't drool. It is a nectar
that is used to
attract prey.

pokedex.name: vileplume
pokedex.flavor_text:
It has the worldâs largest petals. With every step,
the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.

pokedex.name: paras
pokedex.flavor_text:
Burrows to suck
tree roots. The
mushrooms on its back grow by drawÂ­
ing nutrients from
the bug host.

pokedex.name: parasect
pokedex.flavor_text:
A host-parasite
pair in which the
parasite mushroom has taken over the
host bug. Prefers
damp places.

pokedex.name: venonat
pokedex.flavor_text:
Lives in the
shadows of tall
trees where it eats insects. It
is attracted by
light at night.

pokedex.name: venomoth
pokedex.flavor_text:
The dustlike scales covering its wings
are color-coded to indicate the kinds of
poison it has.

pokedex.name: diglett
pokedex.flavor_text:
Lives about one
yard underground
where it feeds on plant roots. It
sometimes appears
above ground.

pokedex.name: dugtrio
pokedex.flavor_text:
A team of DIGLETT
triplets.
It triggers huge earthquakes by
burrowing 60 miles
underground.

pokedex.name: meowth
pokedex.flavor_text:
It washes its face regularly to keep the coin on
its forehead spotless. It doesnât get along with
Galarian Meowth.

pokedex.name: persian
pokedex.flavor_text:
Although its fur
has many admirers,
it is tough to raise as a pet
because of its
fickle meanness.

pokedex.name: psyduck
pokedex.flavor_text:
While lulling its
enemies with its
vacant look, this wily POKÃ©MON will
use psychokinetic
powers.

pokedex.name: golduck
pokedex.flavor_text:
Often seen swimÂ­
ming elegantly by
lake shores. It is often mistaken
for the Japanese
monster, Kappa.

pokedex.name: mankey
pokedex.flavor_text:
Extremely quick to
anger. It could
be docile one moment then
thrashing away
the next instant.

pokedex.name: primeape
pokedex.flavor_text:
Always furious
and tenacious to
boot. It will not abandon chasing
its quarry until
it is caught.

pokedex.name: growlithe
pokedex.flavor_text:
Very protective
of its territory.
It will bark and bite to repel
intruders from
its space.

pokedex.name: arcanine
pokedex.flavor_text:
A POKÃ©MON that
has been admired
since the past for its beauty.
It runs agilely
as if on wings.

pokedex.name: poliwag
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its newly grown
legs prevent it
from running. It appears to prefer
swimming than
trying to stand.

pokedex.name: poliwhirl
pokedex.flavor_text:
Capable of living
in or out of
water. When out of water, it
sweats to keep
its body slimy.

pokedex.name: poliwrath
pokedex.flavor_text:
An adept swimmer
at both the front
crawl and breast stroke. Easily
overtakes the best
human swimmers.

pokedex.name: abra
pokedex.flavor_text:
Using its ability
to read minds, it
will identify impending danger
and TELEPORT to
safety.

pokedex.name: kadabra
pokedex.flavor_text:
It emits special
alpha waves from
its body that induce headaches
just by being
close by.

pokedex.name: alakazam
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its brain can outÂ­
perform a superÂ­
computer. Its intelligence
quotient is said
to be 5,000.

pokedex.name: machop
pokedex.flavor_text:
Loves to build
its muscles.
It trains in all styles of martial
arts to become
even stronger.

pokedex.name: machoke
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its muscular body
is so powerful, it
must wear a power save belt to be
able to regulate
its motions.

pokedex.name: machamp
pokedex.flavor_text:
Using its heavy
muscles, it throws
powerful punches that can send the
victim clear over
the horizon.

pokedex.name: bellsprout
pokedex.flavor_text:
A carnivorous
POKÃ©MON that traps
and eats bugs. It uses its root
feet to soak up
needed moisture.

pokedex.name: weepinbell
pokedex.flavor_text:
It spits out
POISONPOWDER to
immobilize the enemy and then
finishes it with
a spray of ACID.

pokedex.name: victreebel
pokedex.flavor_text:
Said to live in
huge colonies
deep in jungles, although no one
has ever returned
from there.

pokedex.name: tentacool
pokedex.flavor_text:
Drifts in shallow
seas. Anglers who
hook them by accident are
often punished by
its stinging acid.

pokedex.name: tentacruel
pokedex.flavor_text:
The tentacles are
normally kept
short. On hunts, they are extended
to ensnare and
immobilize prey.

pokedex.name: geodude
pokedex.flavor_text:
Found in fields
and mountains.
Mistaking them for boulders,
people often step
or trip on them.

pokedex.name: graveler
pokedex.flavor_text:
Rolls down slopes
to move. It rolls
over any obstacle without slowing
or changing its
direction.

pokedex.name: golem
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its boulder-like
body is extremely
hard. It can easily withstand
dynamite blasts
without damage.

pokedex.name: ponyta
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its hooves are 10
times harder than
diamonds. It can trample anything
completely flat
in little time.

pokedex.name: rapidash
pokedex.flavor_text:
Very competitive,
this POKÃ©MON will
chase anything that moves fast
in the hopes of
racing it.

pokedex.name: slowpoke
pokedex.flavor_text:
Incredibly slow
and dopey. It
takes 5 seconds for it to feel
pain when under
attack.

pokedex.name: slowbro
pokedex.flavor_text:
The SHELLDER that
is latched onto
SLOWPOKE's tail is said to feed
on the host's left
over scraps.

pokedex.name: magnemite
pokedex.flavor_text:
Uses anti-gravity
to stay suspended.
Appears without warning and uses
THUNDER WAVE and
similar moves.

pokedex.name: magneton
pokedex.flavor_text:
Formed by several
MAGNEMITEs linked
together. They frequently appear
when sunspots
flare up.

pokedex.name: farfetchd
pokedex.flavor_text:
The sprig of
green onions it
holds is its weapon. It is
used much like a
metal sword.

pokedex.name: doduo
pokedex.flavor_text:
A bird that makes
up for its poor
flying with its fast foot speed.
Leaves giant
footprints.

pokedex.name: dodrio
pokedex.flavor_text:
Uses its three
brains to execute
complex plans. While two heads
sleep, one head
stays awake.

pokedex.name: seel
pokedex.flavor_text:
The protruding
horn on its head
is very hard. It is used for
bashing through
thick ice.

pokedex.name: dewgong
pokedex.flavor_text:
Stores thermal
energy in its
body. Swims at a steady 8 knots
even in intensely
cold waters.

pokedex.name: grimer
pokedex.flavor_text:
Appears in filthy
areas. Thrives by
sucking up polluted sludge
that is pumped
out of factories.

pokedex.name: muk
pokedex.flavor_text:
Thickly covered
with a filthy,
vile sludge. It is so toxic, even
its footprints
contain poison.

pokedex.name: shellder
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its hard shell
repels any kind
of attack. It is vulnerable
only when its
shell is open.

pokedex.name: cloyster
pokedex.flavor_text:
When attacked, it
launches its
horns in quick volleys. Its
innards have
never been seen.

pokedex.name: gastly
pokedex.flavor_text:
Almost invisible,
this gaseous
POKÃ©MON cloaks the target and
puts it to sleep
without notice.

pokedex.name: haunter
pokedex.flavor_text:
Because of its
ability to slip
through block walls, it is said
to be from anÂ­
other dimension.

pokedex.name: gengar
pokedex.flavor_text:
Under a full moon,
this POKÃ©MON
likes to mimic the shadows of
people and laugh
at their fright.

pokedex.name: onix
pokedex.flavor_text:
As it grows, the
stone portions of
its body harden to become similar
to a diamond, but
colored black.

pokedex.name: drowzee
pokedex.flavor_text:
Puts enemies to
sleep then eats
their dreams. Occasionally gets
sick from eating
bad dreams.

pokedex.name: hypno
pokedex.flavor_text:
When it locks eyes
with an enemy, it
will use a mix of PSI moves such as
HYPNOSIS and
CONFUSION.

pokedex.name: krabby
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its pincers are
not only powerful
weapons, they are used for balance
when walking
sideways.

pokedex.name: kingler
pokedex.flavor_text:
The large pincer
has 10000 hp of
crushing power. However, its huge
size makes it
unwieldy to use.

pokedex.name: voltorb
pokedex.flavor_text:
Usually found in
power plants.
Easily mistaken for a POKÃ© BALL,
they have zapped
many people.

pokedex.name: electrode
pokedex.flavor_text:
It stores electric
energy under very
high pressure. It often explodes
with little or no
provocation.

pokedex.name: exeggcute
pokedex.flavor_text:
Often mistaken
for eggs.
When disturbed, they quickly
gather and attack
in swarms.

pokedex.name: exeggutor
pokedex.flavor_text:
Legend has it that
on rare occasions,
one of its heads will drop off and
continue on as an
EXEGGCUTE.

pokedex.name: cubone
pokedex.flavor_text:
Because it never
removes its skull
helmet, no one has ever seen
this POKÃ©MON's
real face.

pokedex.name: marowak
pokedex.flavor_text:
The bone it holds
is its key weapon.
It throws the bone skillfully
like a boomerang
to KO targets.

pokedex.name: hitmonlee
pokedex.flavor_text:
When in a hurry,
its legs lengthen
progressively. It runs smoothly
with extra long,
loping strides.

pokedex.name: hitmonchan
pokedex.flavor_text:
While apparently
doing nothing, it
fires punches in lightning fast
volleys that are
impossible to see.

pokedex.name: lickitung
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its tongue can be
extended like a
chameleon's. It leaves a tingling
sensation when it
licks enemies.

pokedex.name: koffing
pokedex.flavor_text:
Because it stores
several kinds of
toxic gases in its body, it is
prone to exploding
without warning.

pokedex.name: weezing
pokedex.flavor_text:
Where two kinds
of poison gases
meet, 2 KOFFINGs can fuse into a
WEEZING over many
years.

pokedex.name: rhyhorn
pokedex.flavor_text:
A POKÃ©MON with a
one-track mind.
Once it charges,  it won't stop
running until it
falls asleep.

pokedex.name: rhydon
pokedex.flavor_text:
Protected by an
armor-like hide,
it is capable of living in molten
lava of 3,600
degrees.

pokedex.name: chansey
pokedex.flavor_text:
A rare and elusive
POKÃ©MON that is
said to bring happiness to those
who manage to get
it.

pokedex.name: tangela
pokedex.flavor_text:
The whole body is
swathed with wide
vines that are similar to seaÂ­
weed. Its vines
shake as it walks.

pokedex.name: kangaskhan
pokedex.flavor_text:
The infant rarely
ventures out of
its mother's protective pouch
until it is 3
years old.

pokedex.name: horsea
pokedex.flavor_text:
Known to shoot
down flying bugs
with precision blasts of ink
from the surface
of the water.

pokedex.name: seadra
pokedex.flavor_text:
Capable of swimÂ­
ming backwards by
rapidly flapping its wing-like
pectoral fins and
stout tail.

pokedex.name: goldeen
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its tail fin
billows like an
elegant ballroom dress, giving it
the nickname of
the Water Queen.

pokedex.name: seaking
pokedex.flavor_text:
In the autumn spawning season, they can
be seen swimming powerfully up rivers and
creeks.

pokedex.name: staryu
pokedex.flavor_text:
If its body is torn, it can grow
back if the red core remains.
The core flashes at midnight.

pokedex.name: starmie
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its central core
glows with the
seven colors of the rainbow. Some
people value the
core as a gem.

pokedex.name: mr-mime
pokedex.flavor_text:
If interrupted
while it is
miming, it will slap around the
offender with its
broad hands.

pokedex.name: scyther
pokedex.flavor_text:
With ninja-like
agility and speed,
it can create the illusion that
there is more
than one.

pokedex.name: jynx
pokedex.flavor_text:
It seductively
wiggles its hips
as it walks. It can cause people
to dance in
unison with it.

pokedex.name: electabuzz
pokedex.flavor_text:
Normally found
near power plants,
they can wander away and cause
major blackouts
in cities.

pokedex.name: magmar
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its body always
burns with an
orange glow that enables it to
hide perfectly
among flames.

pokedex.name: pinsir
pokedex.flavor_text:
If it fails to
crush the victim
in its pincers, it will swing it
around and toss
it hard.

pokedex.name: tauros
pokedex.flavor_text:
When it targets
an enemy, it
charges furiously while whipping its
body with its
long tails.

pokedex.name: magikarp
pokedex.flavor_text:
In the distant
past, it was
somewhat stronger than the horribly
weak descendants
that exist today.

pokedex.name: gyarados
pokedex.flavor_text:
Once it begins to rampage, a
GYARADOS will burn everything
down, even in a harsh storm.

pokedex.name: lapras
pokedex.flavor_text:
A POKÃ©MON that
has been overÂ­
hunted almost to extinction. It
can ferry people
across the water.

pokedex.name: ditto
pokedex.flavor_text:
Capable of copying
an enemy's genetic
code to instantly transform itself
into a duplicate
of the enemy.

pokedex.name: eevee
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its genetic code
is irregular.
It may mutate if it is exposed to
radiation from
element STONEs.

pokedex.name: vaporeon
pokedex.flavor_text:
Lives close to
water. Its long
tail is ridged with a fin which
is often mistaken
for a mermaid's.

pokedex.name: jolteon
pokedex.flavor_text:
It accumulates
negative ions in
the atmosphere to blast out 10000-
volt lightning
bolts.

pokedex.name: flareon
pokedex.flavor_text:
When storing
thermal energy in
its body, its temperature could
soar to over 1600
degrees.

pokedex.name: porygon
pokedex.flavor_text:
A POKÃ©MON that
consists entirely
of programming code. Capable of
moving freely in
cyberspace.

pokedex.name: omanyte
pokedex.flavor_text:
Although long
extinct, in rare
cases, it can be genetically
resurrected from
fossils.

pokedex.name: omastar
pokedex.flavor_text:
A prehistoric
POKÃ©MON that died
out when its heavy shell made
it impossible to
catch prey.

pokedex.name: kabuto
pokedex.flavor_text:
A POKÃ©MON that
was resurrected
from a fossil found in what was
once the ocean
floor eons ago.

pokedex.name: kabutops
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its sleek shape is
perfect for swimÂ­
ming. It slashes prey with its
claws and drains
the body fluids.

pokedex.name: aerodactyl
pokedex.flavor_text:
A PokÃ©mon that roamed the skies
in the dinosaur era. Its teeth are
like saw blades.

pokedex.name: snorlax
pokedex.flavor_text:
Very lazy. Just
eats and sleeps.
As its rotund bulk builds, it
becomes steadily
more slothful.

pokedex.name: articuno
pokedex.flavor_text:
A legendary bird
POKÃ©MON that is
said to appear to doomed people who
are lost in icy
mountains.

pokedex.name: zapdos
pokedex.flavor_text:
A legendary bird
POKÃ©MON that is
said to appear from clouds while
dropping enormous
lightning bolts.

pokedex.name: moltres
pokedex.flavor_text:
Known as the
legendary bird of
fire. Every flap of its wings
creates a dazzling
flash of flames.

pokedex.name: dratini
pokedex.flavor_text:
Long considered a
mythical POKÃ©MON
until recently when a small
colony was found
living underwater.

pokedex.name: dragonair
pokedex.flavor_text:
A mystical POKÃ©MON
that exudes a
gentle aura. Has the ability
to change climate
conditions.

pokedex.name: dragonite
pokedex.flavor_text:
An extremely
rarely seen
marine POKÃ©MON. Its intelligence
is said to match
that of humans.

pokedex.name: mewtwo
pokedex.flavor_text:
It was created by
a scientist after
years of horrific gene splicing and
DNA engineering
experiments.

pokedex.name: mew
pokedex.flavor_text:
So rare that it
is still said to
be a mirage by many experts. Only
a few people have
seen it worldwide.

pokedex.name: chikorita
pokedex.flavor_text:
A sweet aroma
gently wafts from
the leaf on its head. It is docile
and loves to soak
up the sun's rays.

pokedex.name: bayleef
pokedex.flavor_text:
The scent of
spices comes from
around its neck. Somehow, sniffing
it makes you want
to fight.

pokedex.name: meganium
pokedex.flavor_text:
The aroma that
rises from its
petals contains a substance that
calms aggressive
feelings.

pokedex.name: cyndaquil
pokedex.flavor_text:
It has a timid nature. If it is startled, the flames on
its back burn more vigorously.

pokedex.name: quilava
pokedex.flavor_text:
Be careful if it
turns its back
during battle. It means that it will
attack with the
fire on its back.

pokedex.name: typhlosion
pokedex.flavor_text:
If its rage peaks,
it becomes so hot
that anything that touches it will
instantly go
up in flames.

pokedex.name: totodile
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its well-developed
jaws are powerful
and capable of crushing anything.
Even its trainer
must be careful.

pokedex.name: croconaw
pokedex.flavor_text:
If it loses a
fang, a new one
grows back in its place. There are
always 48 fangs
lining its mouth.

pokedex.name: feraligatr
pokedex.flavor_text:
When it bites with
its massive and
powerful jaws, it shakes its head
and savagely tears
its victim up.

pokedex.name: sentret
pokedex.flavor_text:
A very cautious
POKÃ©MON, it raises
itself up using its tail to get a
better view of its
surroundings.

pokedex.name: furret
pokedex.flavor_text:
It makes a nest to
suit its long and
skinny body. The nest is impossible
for other POKÃ©MON
to enter.

pokedex.name: hoothoot
pokedex.flavor_text:
It always stands
on one foot. It
changes feet so fast, the movement
can rarely be
seen.

pokedex.name: noctowl
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its eyes are
specially adapted.
They concentrate even faint light
and enable it to
see in the dark.

pokedex.name: ledyba
pokedex.flavor_text:
It is very timid.
It will be afraid
to move if it is alone. But it will
be active if it is
in a group.

pokedex.name: ledian
pokedex.flavor_text:
When the stars
flicker in the
night sky, it flutters about,
scattering a
glowing powder.

pokedex.name: spinarak
pokedex.flavor_text:
It lies still in
the same pose for
days in its web, waiting for its
unsuspecting prey
to wander close.

pokedex.name: ariados
pokedex.flavor_text:
It spins string
not only from its
rear but also from its mouth. It is
hard to tell which
end is which.

pokedex.name: crobat
pokedex.flavor_text:
It flies so siÂ­
lently through the
dark on its four wings that it may
not be noticed
even when nearby.

pokedex.name: chinchou
pokedex.flavor_text:
Chinchou blink their shining antennae at one
another to claim their respective turf.

pokedex.name: lanturn
pokedex.flavor_text:
The light it emits
is so bright that
it can illuminate the sea's surface
from a depth of
over three miles.

pokedex.name: pichu
pokedex.flavor_text:
It is not yet
skilled at storing
electricity. It may send out a
jolt if amused
or startled.

pokedex.name: cleffa
pokedex.flavor_text:
Because of its
unusual, star-like
silhouette, people believe that it
came here on
a meteor.

pokedex.name: igglybuff
pokedex.flavor_text:
It has a very soft
body. If it starts
to roll, it will bounce all over
and be impossible
to stop.

pokedex.name: togepi
pokedex.flavor_text:
The shell seems to
be filled with
joy. It is said that it will share
good luck when
treated kindly.

pokedex.name: togetic
pokedex.flavor_text:
They say that it
will appear before
kindhearted, carÂ­ ing people and
shower them with
happiness.

pokedex.name: natu
pokedex.flavor_text:
Because its wings
aren't yet fully
grown, it has to hop to get around.
It is always starÂ­
ing at something.

pokedex.name: xatu
pokedex.flavor_text:
They say that it
stays still and
quiet because it is seeing both the
past and future at
the same time.

pokedex.name: mareep
pokedex.flavor_text:
If static elecÂ­
tricity builds in
its body, its fleece doubles in
volume. Touching
it will shock you.

pokedex.name: flaaffy
pokedex.flavor_text:
As a result of
storing too much
electricity, it developed patches
where even downy
wool won't grow.

pokedex.name: ampharos
pokedex.flavor_text:
The tail's tip
shines brightly
and can be seen from far away. It
acts as a beacon
for lost people.

pokedex.name: bellossom
pokedex.flavor_text:
Plentiful in the tropics. When it
dances, its petals rub together and
make a pleasant ringing sound.

pokedex.name: marill
pokedex.flavor_text:
The tip of its
tail, which conÂ­
tains oil that is lighter than waÂ­
ter, lets it swim
without drowning.

pokedex.name: azumarill
pokedex.flavor_text:
It lives in water virtually all day long.
Its body color and pattern act as
camouflage that makes it tough for
enemies to spot in water.

pokedex.name: sudowoodo
pokedex.flavor_text:
Although it always
pretends to be a
tree, its composiÂ­ tion appears to be
closer to a rock
than a plant.

pokedex.name: politoed
pokedex.flavor_text:
If POLIWAG and
POLIWHIRL hear its
echoing cry, they respond by gatherÂ­
ing from far and
wide.

pokedex.name: hoppip
pokedex.flavor_text:
To keep from being
blown away by the
wind, they gather in clusters. They
do enjoy gentle
breezes, though.

pokedex.name: skiploom
pokedex.flavor_text:
The bloom on top
of its head opens
and closes as the temperature flucÂ­
tuates up and
down.

pokedex.name: jumpluff
pokedex.flavor_text:
Once it catches
the wind, it deftÂ­
ly controls its cotton-puff spores
to float, even
around the world.

pokedex.name: aipom
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its tail is so
powerful that it
can use it to grab a tree branch and
hold itself up in
the air.

pokedex.name: sunkern
pokedex.flavor_text:
It may drop out of
the sky suddenly.
If attacked by a SPEAROW, it will
violently shake
its leaves.

pokedex.name: sunflora
pokedex.flavor_text:
It converts sunÂ­
light into energy.
In the darkness after sunset, it
closes its petals
and becomes still.

pokedex.name: yanma
pokedex.flavor_text:
If it flaps its
wings really fast,
it can generate shock waves that
will shatter winÂ­
dows in the area.

pokedex.name: wooper
pokedex.flavor_text:
This POKÃ©MON lives
in cold water. It
will leave the water to search
for food when it
gets cold outside.

pokedex.name: quagsire
pokedex.flavor_text:
This carefree
POKÃ©MON has an
easy-going nature. While swimming, it
always bumps into
boat hulls.

pokedex.name: espeon
pokedex.flavor_text:
It uses the fine
hair that covers
its body to sense air currents and
predict its eneÂ­
my's actions.

pokedex.name: umbreon
pokedex.flavor_text:
When agitated,
this POKÃ©MON proÂ­
tects itself by spraying poisonous
sweat from its
pores.

pokedex.name: murkrow
pokedex.flavor_text:
Feared and loathed
by many, it is
believed to bring misfortune to all
those who see it
at night.

pokedex.name: slowking
pokedex.flavor_text:
It has incredible
intellect and inÂ­
tuition. Whatever the situation, it
remains calm and
collected.

pokedex.name: misdreavus
pokedex.flavor_text:
It likes playing
mischievous tricks
such as screaming and wailing to
startle people at
night.

pokedex.name: unown
pokedex.flavor_text:
Their shapes look
like hieroglyphs
on ancient tabÂ­ lets. It is said
that the two are
somehow related.

pokedex.name: wobbuffet
pokedex.flavor_text:
It hates light and
shock. If attackÂ­
ed, it inflates its body to pump
up its counterÂ­
strike.

pokedex.name: girafarig
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its tail has a
small brain of its
own. Beware! If you get close, it
may react to your
scent and bite.

pokedex.name: pineco
pokedex.flavor_text:
It likes to make
its shell thicker
by adding layers of tree bark. The
additional weight
doesn't bother it.

pokedex.name: forretress
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its entire body is
shielded by a
steel-hard shell. What lurks inside
the armor is a
total mystery.

pokedex.name: dunsparce
pokedex.flavor_text:
When spotted, this
POKÃ©MON escapes
backward by furiÂ­ ously boring into
the ground with
its tail.

pokedex.name: gligar
pokedex.flavor_text:
It flies straight
at its target's
face then clamps down on the starÂ­
tled victim to
inject poison.

pokedex.name: steelix
pokedex.flavor_text:
It is thought its body transformed
as a result of iron accumulating
internally from swallowing soil.

pokedex.name: snubbull
pokedex.flavor_text:
Although it looks
frightening, it is
actually kind and affectionate. It
is very popular
among women.

pokedex.name: granbull
pokedex.flavor_text:
It is actually
timid and easily
spooked. If atÂ­ tacked, it flails
about to fend off
its attacker.

pokedex.name: qwilfish
pokedex.flavor_text:
To fire its poison
spikes, it must
inflate its body by drinking over
2.6 gallons of
water all at once.

pokedex.name: scizor
pokedex.flavor_text:
It has a steel-hard body. It
intimidates foes by upraising its
eye-patterned pincers.

pokedex.name: shuckle
pokedex.flavor_text:
The BERRIES it
stores in its
vase-like shell decompose and
become a gooey
liquid.

pokedex.name: heracross
pokedex.flavor_text:
It is usually docile, but if it is
disturbed while sipping honey,
it chases off the intruder with its horn.

pokedex.name: sneasel
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its paws conceal
sharp claws. If
attacked, it sudÂ­ denly extends the
claws and startles
its enemy.

pokedex.name: teddiursa
pokedex.flavor_text:
If it finds honey,
its crescent mark
glows. It always licks its paws
because they are
soaked with honey.

pokedex.name: ursaring
pokedex.flavor_text:
Although it is a
good climber, it
prefers to snap trees with its
forelegs and eat
fallen BERRIES.

pokedex.name: slugma
pokedex.flavor_text:
It never sleeps.
It has to keep
moving because if it stopped, its
magma body would
cool and harden.

pokedex.name: magcargo
pokedex.flavor_text:
The shell on its
back is just skin
that has cooled and hardened. It
breaks easily with
a slight touch.

pokedex.name: swinub
pokedex.flavor_text:
It rubs its snout
on the ground to
find and dig up food. It sometimes
discovers hot
springs.

pokedex.name: piloswine
pokedex.flavor_text:
Because the long
hair all over its
body obscures its sight, it just
keeps charging
repeatedly.

pokedex.name: corsola
pokedex.flavor_text:
It continuously
sheds and grows.
The tip of its head is prized as
a treasure for its
beauty.

pokedex.name: remoraid
pokedex.flavor_text:
It has superb acÂ­
curacy. The water
it shoots out can strike even moving
prey from more
than 300 feet.

pokedex.name: octillery
pokedex.flavor_text:
It traps enemies
with its suction-
cupped tentacles then smashes them
with its rock-hard
head.

pokedex.name: delibird
pokedex.flavor_text:
It carries food
all day long.
There are tales about lost people
who were saved by
the food it had.

pokedex.name: mantine
pokedex.flavor_text:
As it majestically
swims, it doesn't
care if REMORAID attach to it for
scavenging its
leftovers.

pokedex.name: skarmory
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its sturdy wings
look heavy, but
they are actually hollow and light,
allowing it to fly
freely in the sky.

pokedex.name: houndour
pokedex.flavor_text:
It uses different
kinds of cries for
communicating with others of its kind
and for pursuing
its prey.

pokedex.name: houndoom
pokedex.flavor_text:
If you are burned
by the flames it
shoots from its mouth, the pain
will never go
away.

pokedex.name: kingdra
pokedex.flavor_text:
It is said that it
usually hides in
underwater caves. It can create
whirlpools by
yawning.

pokedex.name: phanpy
pokedex.flavor_text:
It swings its long
snout around playÂ­
fully, but because it is so strong,
that can be danÂ­
gerous.

pokedex.name: donphan
pokedex.flavor_text:
It has sharp, hard
tusks and a rugged
hide. Its TACKLE is strong enough
to knock down a
house.

pokedex.name: porygon2
pokedex.flavor_text:
This upgraded
version of PORYGON
is designed for space exploration.
It can't fly,
though.

pokedex.name: stantler
pokedex.flavor_text:
The curved antlers
subtly change the
flow of air to create a strange
space where realÂ­
ity is distorted.

pokedex.name: smeargle
pokedex.flavor_text:
A special fluid
oozes from the tip
of its tail. It paints the fluid
everywhere to mark
its territory.

pokedex.name: tyrogue
pokedex.flavor_text:
It is always
bursting with enÂ­
ergy. To make itÂ­ self stronger, it
keeps on fighting
even if it loses.

pokedex.name: hitmontop
pokedex.flavor_text:
If you become
enchanted by its
smooth, elegant, dance-like kicks,
you may get
drilled hard.

pokedex.name: smoochum
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its lips are the
most sensitive
parts on its body. It always uses its
lips first to
examine things.

pokedex.name: elekid
pokedex.flavor_text:
It rotates its
arms to generate
electricity, but it tires easily,
so it charges up
only a little bit.

pokedex.name: magby
pokedex.flavor_text:
Each and every
time it inhales
and exhales, hot embers dribble out
of its mouth and
nostrils.

pokedex.name: miltank
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its milk is packed
with nutrition,
making it the ultimate beverage
for the sick or
weary.

pokedex.name: blissey
pokedex.flavor_text:
Anyone who takes
even one bite of
BLISSEY's egg beÂ­ comes unfailingly
caring and pleasÂ­
ant to everyone.

pokedex.name: raikou
pokedex.flavor_text:
The rain clouds it
carries let it
fire thunderbolts at will. They say
that it descended
with lightning.

pokedex.name: entei
pokedex.flavor_text:
Volcanoes erupt
when it barks. UnÂ­
able to restrain its extreme power,
it races headlong
around the land.

pokedex.name: suicune
pokedex.flavor_text:
It races around the world to
purify fouled water. It dashes
away with the north wind.

pokedex.name: larvitar
pokedex.flavor_text:
It feeds on soil.
After it has eaten
a large mountain, it will fall
asleep so it can
grow.

pokedex.name: pupitar
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its shell is as
hard as sheet
rock, and it is also very strong.
Its THRASHING can
topple a mountain.

pokedex.name: tyranitar
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its body can't be
harmed by any sort
of attack, so it is very eager to
make challenges
against enemies.

pokedex.name: lugia
pokedex.flavor_text:
It is said that it
quietly spends its
time deep at the bottom of the sea
because its powers
are too strong.

pokedex.name: ho-oh
pokedex.flavor_text:
Legends claim this
POKÃ©MON flies the
world's skies conÂ­ tinuously on its
magnificent seven-
colored wings.

pokedex.name: celebi
pokedex.flavor_text:
This POKÃ©MON wanÂ­
ders across time.
Grass and trees flourish in the
forests in which
it has appeared.

pokedex.name: treecko
pokedex.flavor_text:
TREECKO has small hooks on the bottom
of its feet that enable it to scale
vertical walls. This POKÃ©MON attacks by slamming foes
with its thick tail.

pokedex.name: grovyle
pokedex.flavor_text:
The leaves growing out of GROVYLEâs
body are convenient for camouflaging
it from enemies in the forest. This POKÃ©MON is a master at climbing
trees in jungles.

pokedex.name: sceptile
pokedex.flavor_text:
The leaves growing on SCEPTILEâs body
are very sharp edged. This POKÃ©MON is
very agile - it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe
from above or behind.

pokedex.name: torchic
pokedex.flavor_text:
TORCHIC sticks with its TRAINER,
following behind with unsteady
steps. This POKÃ©MON breathes fire of over
1,800 degrees F, including fireballs
that leave the foe scorched black.

pokedex.name: combusken
pokedex.flavor_text:
COMBUSKEN toughens up its legs and
thighs by running through fields and
mountains. This POKÃ©MONâs legs possess both speed
and power, enabling it to dole out ten
kicks in one second.

pokedex.name: blaziken
pokedex.flavor_text:
In battle, BLAZIKEN blows out intense
flames from its wrists and attacks foes
courageously. The stronger the foe, the more
intensely this POKÃ©MONâs wrists burn.

pokedex.name: mudkip
pokedex.flavor_text:
The fin on MUDKIPâs head acts as highly
sensitive radar. Using this fin to sense
movements of water and air, this POKÃ©MON can determine what is taking
place around it without using its eyes.

pokedex.name: marshtomp
pokedex.flavor_text:
The surface of MARSHTOMPâs body is
enveloped by a thin, sticky film that
enables it to live on land. This POKÃ©MON plays in mud on beaches
when the ocean tide is low.

pokedex.name: swampert
pokedex.flavor_text:
SWAMPERT is very strong. It has enough
power to easily drag a boulder weighing
more than a ton. This POKÃ©MON also has powerful vision
that lets it see even in murky water.

pokedex.name: poochyena
pokedex.flavor_text:
At first sight, POOCHYENA takes a bite
at anything that moves.
This POKÃ©MON chases after prey until the victim becomes exhausted.
However, it may turn tail if the prey
strikes back.

pokedex.name: mightyena
pokedex.flavor_text:
MIGHTYENA gives obvious signals when
it is preparing to attack. It starts to
growl deeply and then flattens its body. This POKÃ©MON will bite savagely with its
sharply pointed fangs.

pokedex.name: zigzagoon
pokedex.flavor_text:
ZIGZAGOON restlessly wanders
everywhere at all times. This POKÃ©MON
does so because it is very curious. It becomes interested in anything
that it happens to see.

pokedex.name: linoone
pokedex.flavor_text:
LINOONE always runs full speed and only
in straight lines. If facing an obstacle,
it makes a right-angle turn to evade it. This POKÃ©MON is very challenged by
gently curving roads.

pokedex.name: wurmple
pokedex.flavor_text:
Using the spikes on its rear end,  
WURMPLE peels the bark off trees and
feeds on the sap that oozes out. This POKÃ©MONâs feet are tipped with
suction pads that allow it to cling to
glass without slipping.

pokedex.name: silcoon
pokedex.flavor_text:
SILCOON tethers itself to a tree branch
using silk to keep from falling. There, 
this POKÃ©MON hangs quietly while it awaits evolution.
It peers out of the silk cocoon through
a small hole.

pokedex.name: beautifly
pokedex.flavor_text:
BEAUTIFLYâs favorite food is the sweet
pollen of flowers. If you want to see
this POKÃ©MON, just leave a potted flower by an open window. BEAUTIFLY
is sure to come looking for pollen.

pokedex.name: cascoon
pokedex.flavor_text:
CASCOON makes its protective cocoon
by wrapping its body entirely with a
fine silk from its mouth. Once the silk goes around its body, it hardens.
This POKÃ©MON prepares for its evolution
inside the cocoon.

pokedex.name: dustox
pokedex.flavor_text:
DUSTOX is instinctively drawn to light.
Swarms of this POKÃ©MON are attracted
by the bright lights of cities, where they wreak havoc by stripping the
leaves off roadside trees for food.

pokedex.name: lotad
pokedex.flavor_text:
It searches about for clean water. If it does not
drink water for too long, the leaf on its head wilts.

pokedex.name: lombre
pokedex.flavor_text:
It lives at the waterâs edge where it is
sunny. It sleeps on a bed of water grass
by day and becomes active at night.

pokedex.name: ludicolo
pokedex.flavor_text:
LUDICOLO begins dancing as soon as
it hears cheerful, festive music.
This POKÃ©MON is said to appear when it hears the singing of children on hiking
outings.

pokedex.name: seedot
pokedex.flavor_text:
SEEDOT attaches itself to a tree
branch using the top of its head.
It sucks moisture from the tree while hanging off the branch.
The more water it drinks, the glossier
this POKÃ©MONâs body becomes.

pokedex.name: nuzleaf
pokedex.flavor_text:
NUZLEAF live in densely overgrown
forests. They occasionally venture out
of the forest to startle people. This POKÃ©MON dislikes having its long
nose pinched.

pokedex.name: shiftry
pokedex.flavor_text:
It lives quietly in the deep forest.
It is said to create chilly winter
winds with the fans it holds.

pokedex.name: taillow
pokedex.flavor_text:
TAILLOW courageously stands its
ground against foes, however strong
they may be. This gutsy POKÃ©MON will remain defiant
even after a loss. On the other hand,
it cries loudly if it becomes hungry.

pokedex.name: swellow
pokedex.flavor_text:
SWELLOW flies high above our heads,
making graceful arcs in the sky.
This POKÃ©MON dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. The hapless
prey is tightly grasped by SWELLOWâs
clawed feet, preventing escape.

pokedex.name: wingull
pokedex.flavor_text:
WINGULL has the habit of carrying prey
and valuables in its beak and hiding
them in all sorts of locations. This POKÃ©MON rides the winds and flies
as if it were skating across the sky.

pokedex.name: pelipper
pokedex.flavor_text:
It is a messenger of the skies,
carrying small PokÃ©mon and
eggs to safety in its bill.

pokedex.name: ralts
pokedex.flavor_text:
RALTS senses the emotions of
people using the horns on its head.
This POKÃ©MON rarely appears before people. But when it does, it draws
closer if it senses that the person has
a positive disposition.

pokedex.name: kirlia
pokedex.flavor_text:
It is said that a KIRLIA that is
exposed to the positive emotions of
its TRAINER grows beautiful. This POKÃ©MON controls psychokinetic
powers with its highly developed brain.

pokedex.name: gardevoir
pokedex.flavor_text:
GARDEVOIR has the ability to read the
future. If it senses impending danger
to its TRAINER, this POKÃ©MON is said to unleash its psychokinetic energy at
full power.

pokedex.name: surskit
pokedex.flavor_text:
From the tips of its feet, SURSKIT
secretes an oil that enables it to walk
on water as if it were skating. This POKÃ©MON feeds on microscopic
organisms in ponds and lakes.

pokedex.name: masquerain
pokedex.flavor_text:
MASQUERAIN intimidates enemies with
the eyelike patterns on its antennas.
This POKÃ©MON flaps its four wings to freely fly in any direction - even
sideways and backwards - as if it were
a helicopter.

pokedex.name: shroomish
pokedex.flavor_text:
SHROOMISH live in damp soil in the dark
depths of forests. They are often
found keeping still under fallen leaves. This POKÃ©MON feeds on compost that
is made up of fallen, rotted leaves.

pokedex.name: breloom
pokedex.flavor_text:
BRELOOM closes in on its foe with light
and sprightly footwork, then throws
punches with its stretchy arms. This POKÃ©MONâs fighting technique puts
boxers to shame.

pokedex.name: slakoth
pokedex.flavor_text:
SLAKOTH lolls around for over twenty
hours every day. Because it moves so
little, it does not need much food. This POKÃ©MONâs sole daily meal consists
of just three leaves.

pokedex.name: vigoroth
pokedex.flavor_text:
VIGOROTH is always itching and agitated
to go on a wild rampage. It simply canât
tolerate sitting still for even a minute. This POKÃ©MONâs stress level rises if it
canât be moving constantly.

pokedex.name: slaking
pokedex.flavor_text:
SLAKING spends all day lying down and
lolling about.
It eats grass growing within its reach. If it eats all the grass it can reach,
this POKÃ©MON reluctantly moves to
another spot.

pokedex.name: nincada
pokedex.flavor_text:
NINCADA lives underground for many
years in complete darkness.
This POKÃ©MON absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees. It stays motionless
as it waits for evolution.

pokedex.name: ninjask
pokedex.flavor_text:
NINJASK moves around at such a high
speed that it cannot be seen, even
while its crying can be clearly heard. For that reason, this POKÃ©MON was long
believed to be invisible.

pokedex.name: shedinja
pokedex.flavor_text:
SHEDINJAâs hard body doesnât move -
not even a twitch. In fact, its body
appears to be merely a hollow shell. It is believed that this POKÃ©MON will
steal the spirit of anyone peering into
its hollow body from its back.

pokedex.name: whismur
pokedex.flavor_text:
Normally, WHISMURâs voice is very quiet -
it is barely audible even if one is
paying close attention. However, if this POKÃ©MON senses danger,
it starts crying at an earsplitting
volume.

pokedex.name: loudred
pokedex.flavor_text:
LOUDREDâs bellowing can completely
decimate a wood-frame house. It uses
its voice to punish its foes. This POKÃ©MONâs round ears serve as
loudspeakers.

pokedex.name: exploud
pokedex.flavor_text:
EXPLOUD triggers earthquakes with the
tremors it creates by bellowing. If this
POKÃ©MON violently inhales from the ports on its body, itâs a sign that it is
preparing to let loose a huge bellow.

pokedex.name: makuhita
pokedex.flavor_text:
MAKUHITA is tenacious - it will keep
getting up and attacking its foe
however many times it is knocked down. Every time it gets back up, this
POKÃ©MON stores more energy in its body
for evolving.

pokedex.name: hariyama
pokedex.flavor_text:
It has the habit of challenging others
without hesitation to tests of strength.
Itâs been known to stand on train tracks
and stop trains using forearm thrusts.

pokedex.name: azurill
pokedex.flavor_text:
A PokÃ©mon that lives by water.
It moves quickly on land by
bouncing on its big tail.

pokedex.name: nosepass
pokedex.flavor_text:
NOSEPASSâs magnetic nose is always
pointed to the north. If two of these
POKÃ©MON meet, they cannot turn their faces to each other when they
are close because their magnetic noses
repel one another.

pokedex.name: skitty
pokedex.flavor_text:
SKITTY has the habit of becoming
fascinated by moving objects and
chasing them around. This POKÃ©MON is known to chase after
its own tail and become dizzy.

pokedex.name: delcatty
pokedex.flavor_text:
DELCATTY prefers to live an unfettered
existence in which it can do as it
pleases at its own pace. Because this POKÃ©MON eats and sleeps
whenever it decides, its daily routines
are completely random.

pokedex.name: sableye
pokedex.flavor_text:
SABLEYE lead quiet lives deep inside
caverns. They are feared, however,
because these POKÃ©MON are thought to steal the spirits of people when their
eyes burn with a sinister glow in the
darkness.

pokedex.name: mawile
pokedex.flavor_text:
MAWHILEâs huge jaws are actually steel
horns that have been transformed.
Its docile-looking face serves to lull its foe into letting down its guard.
When the foe least expects it, MAWHILE
chomps it with its gaping jaws.

pokedex.name: aron
pokedex.flavor_text:
This POKÃ©MON has a body of steel.
To make its body, ARON feeds on
iron ore that it digs from mountains. Occasionally, it causes major trouble by
eating bridges and rails.

pokedex.name: lairon
pokedex.flavor_text:
LAIRON tempers its steel body by
drinking highly nutritious mineral
springwater until it is bloated. This POKÃ©MON makes its nest close to
springs of delicious water.

pokedex.name: aggron
pokedex.flavor_text:
AGGRON claims an entire mountain as its
own territory. It mercilessly beats up
anything that violates its environment. This POKÃ©MON vigilantly patrols its
territory at all times.

pokedex.name: meditite
pokedex.flavor_text:
MEDITITE undertakes rigorous mental
training deep in the mountains.
However, whenever it meditates, this POKÃ©MON always loses its concentration
and focus. As a result, its training
never ends.

pokedex.name: medicham
pokedex.flavor_text:
It is said that through meditation,
MEDICHAM heightens energy inside
its body and sharpens its sixth sense. This POKÃ©MON hides its presence by
merging itself with fields and
mountains.

pokedex.name: electrike
pokedex.flavor_text:
ELECTRIKE stores electricity in its
long body hair. This POKÃ©MON stimulates
its leg muscles with electric charges. These jolts of power give its legs
explosive acceleration performance.

pokedex.name: manectric
pokedex.flavor_text:
MANECTRIC is constantly discharging
electricity from its mane. The sparks
sometimes ignite forest fires. When it enters a battle, this POKÃ©MON
creates thunderclouds.

pokedex.name: plusle
pokedex.flavor_text:
PLUSLE always acts as a cheerleader
for its partners. Whenever a teammate
puts out a good effort in battle, this POKÃ©MON shorts out its body to create
the crackling noises of sparks to show
its joy.

pokedex.name: minun
pokedex.flavor_text:
MINUN is more concerned about cheering
on its partners than its own safety.
It shorts out the electricity in its body to create brilliant showers of
sparks to cheer on its teammates.

pokedex.name: volbeat
pokedex.flavor_text:
With the arrival of night, VOLBEAT emits
light from its tail. It communicates with
others by adjusting the intensity and flashing of its light.
This POKÃ©MON is attracted by the sweet
aroma of ILLUMISE.

pokedex.name: illumise
pokedex.flavor_text:
With its sweet aroma, it guides
Volbeat to draw signs with light in
the night sky.

pokedex.name: roselia
pokedex.flavor_text:
ROSELIA shoots sharp thorns as
projectiles at any opponent that tries
to steal the flowers on its arms. The aroma of this POKÃ©MON brings
serenity to living things.

pokedex.name: gulpin
pokedex.flavor_text:
Virtually all of GULPINâs body is its
stomach. As a result, it can swallow
something its own size. This POKÃ©MONâs stomach contains a
special fluid that digests anything.

pokedex.name: swalot
pokedex.flavor_text:
When SWALOT spots prey, it spurts out
a hideously toxic fluid from its pores
and sprays the target. Once the prey has weakened, this
POKÃ©MON gulps it down whole with its
cavernous mouth.

pokedex.name: carvanha
pokedex.flavor_text:
CARVANHAâs strongly developed jaws
and its sharply pointed fangs pack the
destructive power to rip out boat hulls. Many boats have been attacked and
sunk by this POKÃ©MON.

pokedex.name: sharpedo
pokedex.flavor_text:
Nicknamed âthe bully of the sea,â
SHARPEDO is widely feared.
Its cruel fangs grow back immediately if they snap off.
Just one of these POKÃ©MON can
thoroughly tear apart a supertanker.

pokedex.name: wailmer
pokedex.flavor_text:
WAILMERâs nostrils are located above
its eyes. This playful POKÃ©MON loves
to startle people by forcefully snorting out seawater it stores inside its body
out of its nostrils.

pokedex.name: wailord
pokedex.flavor_text:
WAILORD is the largest of all identified
POKÃ©MON up to now.
This giant POKÃ©MON swims languorously in the vast open sea, eating massive
amounts of food at once with its
enormous mouth.

pokedex.name: numel
pokedex.flavor_text:
NUMEL is extremely dull witted - it
doesnât notice being hit. However, it
canât stand hunger for even a second. This POKÃ©MONâs body is a seething
cauldron of boiling magma.

pokedex.name: camerupt
pokedex.flavor_text:
CAMERUPT has a volcano inside its body.
Magma of 18,000 degrees F courses
through its body. Occasionally, the humps on this
POKÃ©MONâs back erupt, spewing the
superheated magma.

pokedex.name: torkoal
pokedex.flavor_text:
You can tell how itâs feeling by the smoke
spouting from its shell. Tremendous velocity
is a sign of good health.

pokedex.name: spoink
pokedex.flavor_text:
SPOINK bounces around on its tail.
The shock of its bouncing makes its
heart pump. As a result, this POKÃ©MON cannot afford to stop bouncing - if it
stops, its heart will stop.

pokedex.name: grumpig
pokedex.flavor_text:
GRUMPIG uses the black pearls on its
body to amplify its psychic power waves
for gaining total control over its foe. When this POKÃ©MON uses its special
power, its snorting breath grows
labored.

pokedex.name: spinda
pokedex.flavor_text:
No two Spinda have the same
pattern of spots. Its tottering
step fouls the aim of foes.

pokedex.name: trapinch
pokedex.flavor_text:
TRAPINCHâs nest is a sloped, bowl-like
pit dug in sand. This POKÃ©MON patiently
waits for prey to tumble down the pit. Its giant jaws have enough strength
to crush even boulders.

pokedex.name: vibrava
pokedex.flavor_text:
To make prey faint, VIBRAVA generates
ultrasonic waves by vigorously making
its two wings vibrate. This POKÃ©MONâs ultrasonic waves are so
powerful, they can bring on headaches
in people.

pokedex.name: flygon
pokedex.flavor_text:
FLYGON is nicknamed âthe elemental 
spirit of the desert.â Because its
flapping wings whip up a cloud of sand, this POKÃ©MON is always enveloped in a
sandstorm while flying.

pokedex.name: cacnea
pokedex.flavor_text:
CACNEA lives in arid locations such
as deserts. It releases a strong aroma
from its flower to attract prey. When prey comes near, this POKÃ©MON
shoots sharp thorns from its body to
bring the victim down.

pokedex.name: cacturne
pokedex.flavor_text:
During the daytime, CACTURNE remains
unmoving so that it does not lose any
moisture to the harsh desert sun. This POKÃ©MON becomes active at night
when the temperature drops.

pokedex.name: swablu
pokedex.flavor_text:
SWABLU has light and fluffy wings that
are like cottony clouds. This POKÃ©MON
is not frightened of people. It lands on the heads of people and
sits there like a cotton-fluff hat.

pokedex.name: altaria
pokedex.flavor_text:
ALTARIA dances and wheels through the
sky among billowing, cotton-like clouds.
By singing melodies in its crystal-clear voice, this POKÃ©MON makes its listeners
experience dreamy wonderment.

pokedex.name: zangoose
pokedex.flavor_text:
Memories of battling its arch-rival
SEVIPER are etched into every cell of
ZANGOOSEâs body. This POKÃ©MON adroitly dodges attacks
with incredible agility.

pokedex.name: seviper
pokedex.flavor_text:
SEVIPER shares a generations-long
feud with ZANGOOSE. The scars on its
body are evidence of vicious battles. This POKÃ©MON attacks using its sword-
edged tail.

pokedex.name: lunatone
pokedex.flavor_text:
LUNATONE was discovered at a location
where a meteorite fell. As a result, some
people theorize that this POKÃ©MON came from space. However, no one has
been able to prove this theory so far.

pokedex.name: solrock
pokedex.flavor_text:
Solar energy is the source of its power,
so it is strong during the daytime.
When it spins, its body shines.

pokedex.name: barboach
pokedex.flavor_text:
BARBOACHâs sensitive whiskers serve
as a superb radar system.
This POKÃ©MON hides in mud, leaving only its two whiskers exposed while it waits
for prey to come along.

pokedex.name: whiscash
pokedex.flavor_text:
WHISCASH is extremely territorial.
Just one of these POKÃ©MON will claim a
large pond as its exclusive territory. If a foe approaches it, it thrashes
about and triggers a massive
earthquake.

pokedex.name: corphish
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its hardy vitality enables it to
adapt to any environment. Its
pincers will never release prey.

pokedex.name: crawdaunt
pokedex.flavor_text:
CRAWDAUNT has an extremely violent
nature that compels it to challenge
other living things to battle. Other life-forms refuse to live in
ponds inhabited by this POKÃ©MON,
making them desolate places.

pokedex.name: baltoy
pokedex.flavor_text:
BALTOY moves while spinning around on
its one foot. Primitive wall paintings
depicting this POKÃ©MON living among people were discovered in some ancient
ruins.

pokedex.name: claydol
pokedex.flavor_text:
CLAYDOL are said to be dolls of mud made
by primitive humans and brought to life
by exposure to a mysterious ray. This POKÃ©MON moves about while
levitating.

pokedex.name: lileep
pokedex.flavor_text:
LILEEP became extinct approximately
a hundred million years ago.
This ancient POKÃ©MON attaches itself to a rock on the seafloor and catches
approaching prey using tentacles 
shaped like flower petals.

pokedex.name: cradily
pokedex.flavor_text:
CRADILY roams around the ocean floor
in search of food. This POKÃ©MON freely
extends its tree trunk-like neck and captures unwary prey using its eight
tentacles.

pokedex.name: anorith
pokedex.flavor_text:
ANORITH was regenerated from a
prehistoric fossil. This primitive
POKÃ©MON once lived in warm seas. It grips its prey firmly between its
two large claws.

pokedex.name: armaldo
pokedex.flavor_text:
ARMALDOâs tough armor makes all attacks
bounce off. This POKÃ©MONâs two
enormous claws can be freely extended or contracted. They have the power to
punch right through a steel slab.

pokedex.name: feebas
pokedex.flavor_text:
FEEBASâs fins are ragged and
tattered from the start of its life.
Because of its shoddy appearance, this POKÃ©MON is largely ignored.
It is capable of living in both the sea
and in rivers.

pokedex.name: milotic
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its lovely scales are described as
rainbow colored. They change color
depending on the viewing angle.

pokedex.name: castform
pokedex.flavor_text:
CASTFORMâs appearance changes with
the weather.
This POKÃ©MON gained the ability to use the vast power of nature to protect
its tiny body.

pokedex.name: kecleon
pokedex.flavor_text:
It changes body color to blend in with
its surroundings. It also changes color if
it is happy or sad.

pokedex.name: shuppet
pokedex.flavor_text:
SHUPPET is attracted by feelings
of jealousy and vindictiveness.
If someone develops strong feelings of vengeance, this POKÃ©MON will appear
in a swarm and line up beneath the eaves
of that personâs home.

pokedex.name: banette
pokedex.flavor_text:
BANETTE generates energy for laying
strong curses by sticking pins into its
own body. This POKÃ©MON was originally a pitiful
plush doll that was thrown away.

pokedex.name: duskull
pokedex.flavor_text:
DUSKULL can pass through any wall no
matter how thick it may be.
Once this POKÃ©MON chooses a target, it will doggedly pursue the intended
victim until the break of dawn.

pokedex.name: dusclops
pokedex.flavor_text:
DUSCLOPSâs body is completely hollow -
there is nothing at all inside.
It is said that its body is like a black hole. This POKÃ©MON will absorb anything
into its body, but nothing will ever come
back out.

pokedex.name: tropius
pokedex.flavor_text:
The bunches of fruit around TROPIUSâs
neck are very popular with children.
This POKÃ©MON loves fruit, and eats it continuously. Apparently, its love for
fruit resulted in its own outgrowth
of fruit.

pokedex.name: chimecho
pokedex.flavor_text:
CHIMECHO makes its cries echo
inside its hollow body. When this
POKÃ©MON becomes enraged, its cries result in ultrasonic waves that have
the power to knock foes flying.

pokedex.name: absol
pokedex.flavor_text:
Every time ABSOL appears before people,
it is followed by a disaster such as an
earthquake or a tidal wave. As a result, it came to be known as the
disaster POKÃ©MON.

pokedex.name: wynaut
pokedex.flavor_text:
WYNAUT can always be seen with a big,
happy smile on its face. Look at its tail
to determine if it is angry. When angered, this POKÃ©MON will be
slapping the ground with its tail.

pokedex.name: snorunt
pokedex.flavor_text:
SNORUNT live in regions with heavy
snowfall. In seasons without snow, such
as spring and summer, this POKÃ©MON steals away to live quietly among
stalactites and stalagmites deep in
caverns.

pokedex.name: glalie
pokedex.flavor_text:
GLALIE has a body made of rock, which it
hardens with an armor of ice.
This POKÃ©MON has the ability to freeze moisture in the atmosphere into any
shape it desires.

pokedex.name: spheal
pokedex.flavor_text:
SPHEAL is much faster rolling than 
walking to get around. When groups of
this POKÃ©MON eat, they all clap at once to show their pleasure. Because of this,
their mealtimes are noisy.

pokedex.name: sealeo
pokedex.flavor_text:
SEALEO has the habit of always juggling
on the tip of its nose anything it sees
for the first time. This POKÃ©MON occasionally entertains
itself by balancing and rolling a SPHEAL
on its nose.

pokedex.name: walrein
pokedex.flavor_text:
It swims through icy seas while shattering
ice floes with its large tusks. It is
protected by its thick blubber.

pokedex.name: clamperl
pokedex.flavor_text:
CLAMPERLâs sturdy shell is not only good
for protection - it is also used for
clamping and catching prey. A fully grown CLAMPERLâs shell will be
scored with nicks and scratches all
over.

pokedex.name: huntail
pokedex.flavor_text:
HUNTAILâs presence went unnoticed by
people for a long time because it lives
at extreme depths in the sea. This POKÃ©MONâs eyes can see clearly
even in the murky dark depths of the
ocean.

pokedex.name: gorebyss
pokedex.flavor_text:
GOREBYSS lives in the southern seas
at extreme depths. Its body is built to
withstand the enormous pressure of water at incredible depths. Because of
this, this POKÃ©MONâs body is unharmed
by ordinary attacks.

pokedex.name: relicanth
pokedex.flavor_text:
RELICANTH is a POKÃ©MON species that
existed for a hundred million years
without ever changing its form. This ancient POKÃ©MON feeds on
microscopic organisms with its
toothless mouth.

pokedex.name: luvdisc
pokedex.flavor_text:
LUVDISC live in shallow seas in the
tropics. This heart-shaped POKÃ©MON
earned its name by swimming after loving couples it spotted in the
oceanâs waves.

pokedex.name: bagon
pokedex.flavor_text:
Dreaming of one day flying, it practices by leaping
off cliffs every day.

pokedex.name: shelgon
pokedex.flavor_text:
Inside SHELGONâs armor-like shell, cells
are in the midst of transformation
to create an entirely new body. This POKÃ©MONâs shell is extremely heavy,
making its movements sluggish.

pokedex.name: salamence
pokedex.flavor_text:
SALAMENCE came about as a result of a
strong, long-held dream of growing
wings. It is said that this powerful desire triggered a sudden mutation in
this POKÃ©MONâs cells, causing it to
sprout its magnificent wings.

pokedex.name: beldum
pokedex.flavor_text:
Instead of blood, a powerful magnetic
force courses throughout BELDUMâs
body. This POKÃ©MON communicates with others by sending controlled pulses of
magnetism.

pokedex.name: metang
pokedex.flavor_text:
When two BELDUM fuse together, METANG
is formed. The brains of the BELDUM are
joined by a magnetic nervous system. By linking its brains magnetically,
this POKÃ©MON generates strong
psychokinetic power.

pokedex.name: metagross
pokedex.flavor_text:
METAGROSS has four brains in total.
Combined, the four brains can breeze
through difficult calculations faster than a supercomputer.
This POKÃ©MON can float in the air by
tucking in its four legs.

pokedex.name: regirock
pokedex.flavor_text:
Its entire body is made of rock.
If any part chips off in battle, it
attaches rocks to repair itself.

pokedex.name: regice
pokedex.flavor_text:
REGICEâs body was made during an ice
age. The deep-frozen body canât be
melted, even by fire. This POKÃ©MON controls frigid air of
minus 328 degrees F.

pokedex.name: registeel
pokedex.flavor_text:
REGISTEEL has a body that is harder
than any kind of metal.
Its body is apparently hollow. No one has any idea what this POKÃ©MON
eats.

pokedex.name: latias
pokedex.flavor_text:
LATIAS is highly sensitive to the
emotions of people. If it senses any
hostility, this POKÃ©MON ruffles the feathers all over its body and cries
shrilly to intimidate the foe.

pokedex.name: latios
pokedex.flavor_text:
LATIOS has the ability to make its foe
see an image of what it has seen or
imagines in its head. This POKÃ©MON is intelligent and
understands human speech.

pokedex.name: kyogre
pokedex.flavor_text:
KYOGRE has the power to create massive
rain clouds that cover the entire sky
and bring about torrential downpours. This POKÃ©MON saved people who were
suffering from droughts.

pokedex.name: groudon
pokedex.flavor_text:
GROUDON has long been described in 
mythology as the POKÃ©MON that raised
lands and expanded continents. This POKÃ©MON took to sleep after a
cataclysmic battle with KYOGRE.

pokedex.name: rayquaza
pokedex.flavor_text:
RAYQUAZA lived for hundreds of millions
of years in the earthâs ozone layer, 
never descending to the ground. This POKÃ©MON appears to feed on water
and particles in the atmosphere.

pokedex.name: jirachi
pokedex.flavor_text:
A legend states that JIRACHI will make
true any wish that is written on notes
attached to its head when it awakens. If this POKÃ©MON senses danger, it will
fight without awakening.
